{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2011}} {{Infobox organization |name = European Network of Transmission System Operators for Gas |image = ENTSOG logo.jpg |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = ENTSOG |motto = |predecessor = GTE |successor = |formation = {{Start date and years ago|df=yes|2009|12|01}} |extinction = |type = association |status = |purpose = to promote the completion and functioning of the internal market and cross-border trade for gas in the EU |headquarters = Avenue de Cortenbergh 100 / Kortenberglaan 100 |location = [[Brussels]], Belgium |region_served = Europe |membership = [[transmission system operator]]s |language = English |leader_title = President |leader_name = Stephan Kamphues |leader_title2= General Manager |leader_name2 = Vittorio Musazzi |main_organ = General Assembly |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.entsog.eu www.entsog.eu] |remarks = }}
The '''European Network of Transmission System Operators for Gas''' ('''ENTSOG''') is an association of Europe's [[transmission system operator]]s (TSOs). ENTSOG was created on 1 December 2009 by 31&nbsp;TSOs from 21&nbsp;European countries. Creation of the ENTSOG was initiated by the adoption of the European Union [[Third Energy Package|third legislative package on the gas and electricity markets]]. It aims to promote the completion and cross-border trade for gas on the [[Single market of the European Union|European internal market]], and development of the European natural gas transmission network. According to the third energy package ENTSOG is required to develop an EU-wide ten-year gas network development plan.<ref name=euro140610> {{Cite press release | title = Regulators want integrated EU approach to gas | work=Europolitics | author=Dafydd ab Iago | date = 14 June 2010 | url = http://www.europolitics.info/sectorial-policies/regulators-want-integrated-eu-approach-to-gas-art274918-14.html | accessdate =1 July 2010}} </ref>
==Members== ENTSOG now comprises 45 TSOs and 2 Associated Partners from 26 countries and 6 observing TSOs from EU affiliated countries:<ref>ENTSOG Member Companies, http://www.entsog.eu/members</ref>
