{{For|the Jupiter moon|Hegemone (moon)}}
{{Refimprove|date=September 2014}}
'''Hegemone''' (Ἡγεμόνη) was a Greek goddess of [[plants]], specifically making them bloom and bear fruit.
According to [[Pausanias (geographer)|Pausanias]], '''Hegemone''' was a name given by the [[Athens|Athenians]] to one of the [[Charites|Graces]]. [[Auxo]] represented the spring, and Hegemone autumn.<ref>[[Adrian Room]]. ''Who's Who in Classical Mythology'', P. 151 [https://books.google.com/books?id=hl1fkMszwZgC&q=hegemone+autumn&dq=hegemone+autumn&hl=zh-CN&sa=X&ei=myv3UsiFJ82HiQfjpIGwAg&ved=0CC4Q6AEwAA]</ref>

