{{Orphan|date=June 2013}}
'''Valid Time Event Code''' ('''VTEC''') is a [[code]] used by the [[National Weather Service]], a part of [[National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration]] (NOAA) of the [[United States]] [[Federal government of the United States|government]], to identify products / events.<ref>{{cite web|title=Valid Time Event Code (VTEC)|url=http://www.nws.noaa.gov/om/vtec/|work=National Weather Service|accessdate=27 June 2013}}</ref>

